2 Roles
Each member was assigned a feature to work on, the following is a description of these features as well as
the time needed to complete them.
2.1 Core matching system
People working on the core matching system will handle everything related to how requests and offers are
stored in the database, the matching algorithm and the AI matching system.
2.2 Notification system
Users should be notified when someone joins a ride, when a matching ride is available or when a ride is
canceled. This group should handle integration with the Odoo Discussion module, so that passengers and
drivers can communicate easily.
2.3 Map View
The map view should help users visualize offers and requests that are close to their location, so that they
can easily accept them if they want.
2.4 List View
The list view displays offers and requests in a scrollable list format rather than on a map. It’s ideal for users
who prefer structured information over visual maps.
2.5 Templating system
The point of this feature is to let users save commonly used ride details as reusable templates to save time.
